      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence validation — relative hemolysis index",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) study across three mesh refinement levels (coarse 1.8M, medium 4.2M, fine 9.6M cells). GCI for RH index at worst-case operating point is 2.3%, below the 5% acceptance threshold. Discretization error is adequately controlled.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/uq-mesh-gci-301",
        "type": "UncertaintyQuantification",
        "method": "Grid Convergence Index (GCI)",
        "value": 0.023,
        "unit": "dimensionless",
        "description": "GCI-based discretization uncertainty for RH index at 5 L/min, 3000 RPM operating point."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-cpb-experimental-comparison-301",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental comparison — hemolysis index across 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared against in-vitro measurements across all five flow-speed combinations. Mean absolute error is 8.4% with maximum deviation of 14.1% at the highest shear operating point. All predictions fall within the acceptance band defined by the predicate device comparison. The simulation framework is considered validated for the intended regulatory purpose."
    }
  ],
